In a food processor fitted with the metal blade or in a blender, process garlic until minced. Add tuna, 3 tablespoons of the capers, 1 teaspoon brine from capers, cream cheese, lemon juice, and olive oil. Process until smooth. Spoon mixture into a crock or serving bowl. Cover and refrigerate until serving. Before serving, garnish top with a ring of extra capers and green onions. Spread on crackers.